      About this item

      • Apple HomeKit Outlet: Works with Apple homekit to support on and off capabilities.
      • No hub required for set up: Immediately start controlling your plug with quick and easy set up using Bluetooth on your compatible Apple iOS device.
      • Indoor Smart Plug in: Ideal for holiday decorations, fans, small Electronics, floor lamps, table lamps, and more. For indoor use only.
      • Extended features with required Home Hub: control your lights or electronics when you are away from home and create schedules to automatically turn your plug on and off at designated times using compatible Apple TV, HomePod, or iPad.
      • Siri Voice Control: Ask Siri to turn your plug on and off.

      From the manufacturer

      Experience the Convenience of Home Automation with SYLVANIA SMART+

      Having a Smart Home is easy thanks to SYLVANIA SMART+ and Apple HomeKit. In just a few simple steps, you can quickly and easily set up and start controlling your outlet. No hub is required to get started. All you need is your iPhone, iPad, or iPod Touch and your SYLVANIA SMART+ Plug. Can't remember if you left something on? With your SYLVANIA SMART+ Plug and Apple HomeKit, you can monitor and control the device connected to your outlet right from your iPhone or iPad. Use it to control your small electronics, fans, indoor holiday decorations, and more.

      Dont worry about leaving loved ones in the dark

      Schedule lights for everyone in your family - even your pets - after dark when you use your SYLVANIA Apple HomeKit SMART+ Plug with a compatible Apple TV, HomePod, or iPad. This can also help make sure your plug is off when you leave and on when you come home.

      Vintage style with SMART+ convenience

      Add modern controllability to vintage lights by using a SYLVANIA SMART+ Plug.

      Easily control your indoor holiday decorations

      Never worry about having to get out of bed if you forgot to turn off your indoor holiday decorations. Ask Siri to take care of it for you or set up schedules when you use your SYLVANIA SMART+ Plug with a compatible Apple TV, HomePod, or iPad.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Also, I pre-ordered the device on Amazon, because it was not yet available. The wait time was about 3 weeks. Anyway, my home automation setup is simple - I have an Apple Homepod that I use primarily as a hub for home automation. I use the Apple Ecosystem because it is straightforward and does not require a lot of 3rd party apps to automate smart products, and I don't have a lot of time to invest on home automation science projects. The SMART 74582 Smart-plug device does not require a hub to setup. I am not using any app that may (or may not) be available from Sylvania, so I am not rating that. The setup of this device was simple, plug it in, get your phone, go to the Apple Home app, add a device, and scan the small instruction booklet setup graphic that came with the Sylvania device. It worked the first time, no issues. I can issue voice commands to Siri to toggle it off/on, and since I have a hub, I can do this from anywhere my iPhone is wifi/cell connected. I chose to use this device to automate a table lamp that requires a smaller profile lightbulb. I have the SYLVANIA SMART+ Bluetooth Soft White Dimmable A19 LED Bulb, and they work very well. But some table lamps require a smaller lightbulb, and are also too small for a socket automation device. Also, some table lamps have lightbulbs with higher output bulbs than the Sylvania SMART+, cannot use a socket automation device, so the Smart Plug is an excellent solution. The drawback is that the device, that I know of, cannot dim the lightbulb - but I could not dim it before, so no real loss in functionality. The profile of the Sylvania 74582 is so that it does not take space away from the other outlet - it is offset - which is a very well thought out design. The plug is 3-prong (US) male. Conversely, I purchased the Koogeek Smart Plug, WiFi Socket Outlet for Apple HomeKit with Siri (Electronics Controller on 2.4GHz Network) back in Dec-2017, and was not satisfied with it - the product would not setup on my ASUS RT-AC66U router - it kept telling me I had an incompatible Wifi network. However, it configured itself perfectly on my girlfirend's antique D-Link router, so I gifted it to her. I like the products that I have from Sylvania - the SMART+ bulb (non-color), and the SMART 74582 plug. However, the Koogeek proved to minimize the space on the wall outlet to where it was difficult to plug in other cords. Regarding automation with Homekit, it is as easy as any other device, but my needs are basic at this time - turn the device on at a certain time, such as sunset +1 hours, and turn it off at a certain time, and then respond to Siri through voice commands to turn it on/off. It also has button on the front that can turn the outlet on and off manually as needed. Overall, I'm pleased that Sylvania produced a well thought-out product that is compatible with Apple Homekit.
